```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <title>Mark and Code</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.3.1/css/bootstrap.min.css">

  <style>
    body {
      background-color: #fffaf2;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 30px;
    }

    h2 {
      color: #d35400;
      margin-top: 25px;
    }

    mark {
      background-color: yellow;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    code {
      background-color: #f4f4f4;
      color: #c0392b;
      padding: 3px 6px;
      border-radius: 5px;
    }

    hr {
      border-color: #d35400;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <p class="display-1">WEB BASICS</p>
  <p class="display-2">Text Formatting Tags</p>
  <p class="display-3">Learn HTML Easily</p>
  <p class="display-4">Formatting Guide <small>by Student</small></p>

  <hr>

  <h2>Using Mark Tag</h2>
  <p>We use the <mark>mark</mark> tag to highlight important text.</p>
  <p>This sentence shows how to highlight a <mark>key word</mark> in HTML.</p>

  <hr>

  <h2>Using Code Tag</h2>
  <p>The <code>code</code> tag is used to show computer code.</p>
  <p>Example: <code>print("Hello World")</code></p>

  <hr>

  <h2>Combination Example</h2>
  <p>You can also combine both: <mark><code>HTML</code></mark> is a web language.</p>

</body>
</html>
